The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 03 June is 42,322 (4,898.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 29 May, there were 102 new confirmed cases (11.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 22 May, there were 43 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 137% (59 extra cases).
